abstract: Commerce Dept says new single-family-home sales fell 9.2 percent in January to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 494,000 units, compared to 544,000 units in December; says overall housing market recovery remains on track.

headline.print_headline: Sales of New Homes Fell 9% in January, Reversing Course
headline.main: Single-Family Home Sales Fell 9% in January; Services Sector Weakens

snippet: The Commerce Department said home sales fell 9.2 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 494,000 units, almost unwinding December’s increase.
lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department said home sales fell 9.2 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 494,000 units, almost unwinding December’s increase.
